what are pointers ? 
pointers perform the function of storing the addresses of other variables could be int ,char,function,arrays
in c programming pointers are also called reference variable because its responsible for storing address of other variables pointer can store address of same type variable means int pointer only hold the address of int variable 
but the size of pointer is depend upon architecture if 32-bit architecture are thier the pointer size is 2 bytes.

basic syntax of pointer 

int x =10;
int *p =&x;



use of pointer in c 

* is a pointer operators 

operators	|	name	|uses and meaning operators

	*			|ASTERISK | declares a pointer in a program
								Returns the referenced variable's value
								



		
